===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

{{Han compound|萬|虫|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=creature}}. This character represents the original meaning of {{zh-l|*萬}}.

===Etymology===
From {{och-l|厲|sharp}} with a nominalizing devoicing, a realization of a {{cog|sit}} prefix ''*s-'', probably the one used in words for animals ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}} reconstruct it with an additional animal prefix ''*m-''. It may also be connected to {{och-l|蜇|to sting}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

